3e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cimg width=\"368\" height=\"550\" data-src=\"https://www.yatzer.com/sites/default/files/styles/teaser/public/09_paris_apartment_wood_marsh_tommaso_sartori_yatzer.jpg?itok=XBx2vNND\" alt=\"An Art-Led Dialogue Between Heritage and Modernity: Wood Marsh\u0026#39;s Renovation of a Parisian Apartment\" title=\"An Art-Led Dialogue Between Heritage and Modernity: Wood Marsh\u0026#39;s Renovation of a Parisian Apartment\" src=\"https://www.yatzer.com/sites/default/files/styles/teaser/public/09_paris_apartment_wood_marsh_tommaso_sartori_yatzer.jpg?itok=XBx2vNND\"/\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003ch3\u003eAn Art-Led Dialogue Between Heritage and Modernity: Wood Marsh\u0026#39;s Renovation of a Parisian Apartment\u003c/h3\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e  \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\n\u003csection id=\"main\"\u003e\n  \n  \n\n  \n  \u003csection\u003e\n\n        \n    \n  \n\n  \n\n\u003cdiv id=\"hero\"\u003e    \u003cp\u003ePhotography by Tiago Ventura Sales.\u003c/p\u003e  \n  \u003cdiv\u003e\n      \u003cp\u003e\n  \u003ch2\u003eBlending Heritage with Modernity: Zara\u0026#39;s New Pastelaria in Lisbon\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003c/p\u003e    \u003c/div\u003e\n\n  \n      \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003csection\u003e\n\n      \u003cdiv\u003e\n        \u003cdiv\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003ch5\u003eProject Name\u003c/h5\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003eZara by Castro\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003ch5\u003eLocation\u003c/h5\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003ctable\u003e\u003cthead\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003cth colspan=\"6\"\u003eDetailed Information\u003c/th\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003c/thead\u003e\u003ctbody\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd\u003eProject Name\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd\u003eZara by Castro\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd\u003ePosted in\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.yatzer.com/design/interior-design\"\u003eInterior Design\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd\u003eLocation\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd\u003e\n  \u003cdiv\u003e\n    \u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp\u003e3C Praça da Figueira\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003e1100-240\u003c/span\u003e \u003cspan\u003eLisboa\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan\u003ePortugal\u003c/span\u003e  \u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd\u003eCompleted\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd\u003eSeptember 2024\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003c/tbody\u003e\u003c/table\u003e      \u003c/div\u003e\n      \n    \u003cdiv\u003e\n          \n  \u003cp\u003eHoused in a historic 18th-century building in Lisbon’s Praça Dom Pedro IV, popularly known as Rossio Square—one of the most emblematic locations in the Portuguese capital—the new \u003cstrong\u003eZara\u003c/strong\u003e store, which opened its doors in September, is the latest example of the brand’s ambitious new retail concept: expansive flagship stores featuring ‘boutique’ spaces and unique experiences, including in this case a pastelaria, a patisserie serving traditional pastéis de nata (Portuguese custard tarts). In a collaboration with the acclaimed pastry atelier \u003ca href=\"https://castropasteisdenata.pt/en/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eCastro\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/a\u003e, ‘\u003cstrong\u003eZara by Castro\u003c/strong\u003e’ seamlessly marries heritage and modernity, thanks to the thoughtful renovation by \u003ca href=\"https://contactoatlantico.com/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eContacto Atlântico\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/a\u003e and\u003cstrong\u003e \u003ca href=\"https://www.elsaurquijo.com/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eElsa Urquijo Architects\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/strong\u003e, and the bold scenography and playful visual identity developed by \u003ca href=\"https://wozere.com/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eWozere Studio\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eStraddling Praça Dom Pedro IV and Praça da Figueira, the historic building was constructed in the 18th century in the Pombaline style, named after the Marquis of Pombal, who led the city\u0026#39;s reconstruction following the devastating earthquake of 1755. \u003cstrong\u003eDuring the three-year renovation, the architects meticulously restored the building\u0026#39;s rich architectural heritage, from its stone-carved façades and grand staircases to decorative details like ceiling frescoes, stucco mouldings, and over 20,000 traditional tiles.\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n\n      \n  \n\n\u003cdiv\u003e\n  \n  \n\n\n  \n  \u003cfigure\u003e\n    \u003cimg data-original-src=\"https://www.yatzer.com/sites/default/files/media/slideshow/07_zara_lisboa_rossio_pasteleria_wozere_studio_tiago_ventura_sales_yatzer.jpg\" src=\"https://www.yatzer.com/sites/default/files/media/slideshow/07_zara_lisboa_rossio_pasteleria_wozere_studio_tiago_ventura_sales_yatzer.jpg\" width=\"1280\" height=\"1920\" alt=\"Photography by Tiago Ventura Sales.\" title=\"Photography by Tiago Ventura Sales.\" data-src=\"https://www.yatzer.com/sites/default/files/media/slideshow/07_zara_lisboa_rossio_pasteleria_wozere_studio_tiago_ventura_sales_yatzer.jpg\" data-old-src=\"data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEKAAEALAAAAAABAAEAAAICTAEAOw==\"/\u003e\u003cfigcaption\u003e\n\n  \n      \u003cp\u003ePhotography by Tiago Ventura Sales.\u003c/p\u003e\n  \n\u003c/figcaption\u003e\n  \u003c/figure\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n  \n\n\u003cdiv\u003e\n  \n  \n\n\n  \n  \u003cfigure\u003e\n    \u003cimg data-original-src=\"https://www.yatzer.com/sites/default/files/media/slideshow/16_zara_lisboa_rossio_pasteleria_wozere_studio_tiago_ventura_sales_yatzer.jpg\" src=\"https://www.yatzer.com/sites/default/files/media/slideshow/16_zara_lisboa_rossio_pasteleria_wozere_studio_tiago_ventura_sales_yatzer.jpg\" width=\"1280\" heigh